Who's News:
   Wells Fargo's Petrone
   To Resign; Company
   Names 2 Successors
His responsibilities will be assumed by Charles Johnson
and Michael Gillfillan, both of whom are to be promoted to
vice chairman from executive vice president. Mr. Johnson has
been responsible for corporate banking and Mr. Gillfillan has
been overseeing the loan adjustment group.
   The banking company recently reported a 97% plunge in its
1991 net income to $21 million, with bad-loan reserves nearly
doubling to $1.65 billion. The spokeswoman said Mr. Petrone's
departure was unrelated to the bank's earnings.
   Mr. Petrone couldn't be reached for comment.